<p><font face="Verdana" size="5">Object Context: Each context is represented as 
an Object called an Object Context</font></p>

<p><font face="Verdana" size="5"> 
Extension of OOP model to represent even sub-processes as Objects</font></p>

<p></p>

<p><font face="Verdana" size="5" color="#FF0000">Key point:</font></p>

<p><font face="Verdana" size="5" color="#FF0000">Object Contexts are used to 
handle interaction among multiple sub-processes in a
transparent manner</font></p>

<p></p>

